# Grout Design System

## Philosophy

Typography-first, extreme minimalism. Let the words do the work. Every element must earn its place — if it doesn't serve a clear purpose, remove it. Inspired by Sesame, Linear, and Vercel.

## Color

- **Primary**: Orange — `--primary: 24.6 95% 53.1%` in `globals.css`
- **Color restraint**: Orange appears ONLY on CTAs and small brand accents. Everything else is black + gray + white.
- **Background**: Off-white `#fafafa`, not pure white
- **Semantic tokens only** — never hardcode `bg-orange-*` / `text-orange-*`:
  - `bg-primary` / `text-primary` / `text-primary-foreground`
  - `bg-primary/10` for tinted backgrounds
  - `hover:bg-primary/90` for hover states
  - `border-primary/20` for subtle borders
- **Neutral palette**: `gray-900` for headings, `gray-400` for secondary text, `gray-200` for borders, `gray-50` for subtle fills
- **Status colors** (used sparingly): green = success, red = error, amber = warning, blue = info

## Typography

- **Two fonts**: Lora (`font-serif`, `--font-lora`) for headings, DM Sans (`font-sans`, `--font-dm-sans`) for everything else. Both loaded in `layout.tsx`, mapped to `font-serif` and `font-sans` in `tailwind.config.ts`.
- **Serif/sans contrast IS the design** — the pairing creates visual tension. Headings and display numbers are serif, body is sans. Never mix.
- **Heading sizes**: Large — `text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl` for hero h1, `text-3xl sm:text-4xl` for section headings
- **Serif weight**: Lora supports 400–700. Use `font-semibold` on headings for presence.
- **Secondary text**: `text-gray-400` for subtitles, `text-gray-300` for disclaimers
- **Labels/eyebrows**: `text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 font-medium` — subtle, never loud
- **Stats/numbers**: Use `font-sans font-bold` for inline stat numbers, not serif

```tsx
// ✅ Serif heading + sans body
<h1 className="font-serif font-semibold text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl leading-[1.05] text-gray-900">
  Never miss<br />a call again
</h1>
<p className="text-xl text-gray-400 max-w-md leading-relaxed">Subtitle in DM Sans</p>

// ✅ Serif on large display numbers
<span className="font-serif text-5xl text-gray-900">$299</span>

// ❌ Sans on headings (loses the editorial feel)
<h1 className="font-sans text-5xl font-bold">...</h1>
```

## Visual Style

- **Flat design** — zero shadows on cards, containers, or any UI element
- **No exceptions** for shadows except: CTA buttons may optionally have `shadow-sm`
- **No gradients** on surfaces
- **No decorative elements** — no icon containers with colored backgrounds, no badge pills for labels. Use plain text instead.
- **Borders**: `border-gray-100` for subtle dividers, `border-gray-200` for card borders
- **Rounded corners**: `rounded-lg` for CTAs/buttons, `rounded-2xl` for cards/containers, `rounded-lg` for smaller elements

## Spacing

- **Generous whitespace** — err on MORE space. Whitespace is a design element.
- **Hero**: `pt-24 sm:pt-32 lg:pt-40` — push content down, let it breathe
- **Sections**: `py-24` minimum between major sections
- **Grid gaps**: `gap-16 lg:gap-20` for hero grid, `gap-6` for card grids
- **Inner spacing**: `space-y-10` for hero content blocks, `space-y-6` for content groups within

## Components

### Buttons

- Primary CTA: `bg-primary hover:bg-primary/90 text-primary-foreground rounded-lg px-8`
- Secondary: `bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white`
- Use `isLoading` prop, never `disabled`
- Icons inside `<Button>` need NO margin — button has `gap-2`
- **Never use `asChild` on `<Button>` when it has multiple children** (icon + text). Radix `Slot` calls `React.Children.only` and crashes. Instead, wrap `<Button>` inside `<Link>`:
  ```tsx
  // ❌ Crashes — Slot expects a single child element
  <Button asChild><Link href="/"><Icon /> Text</Link></Button>

  // ✅ Works — Link wraps Button, no Slot involved
  <Link href="/"><Button><Icon /> Text</Button></Link>
  ```
- Only one primary CTA per section — don't dilute with secondary buttons

### Cards

- `border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl` — no shadow
- Highlighted card: `border-gray-900 border-2` — dark border, not colored
- No hover effects on cards

### Stats

- Inline text, not boxed components: `<strong className="text-gray-900 text-lg">35-80%</strong> calls missed`
- No icon containers, no colored backgrounds

### Nav

- `bg-[#fafafa]/80 backdrop-blur-sm sticky top-0 z-50`
- Logo: icon + text, no background container on the icon
- Minimal links — only what's essential
- One CTA button: `rounded-lg`

### Footer

- Minimal: logo + copyright. Nothing else needed.
- Use `text-gray-400` for all footer text, `text-gray-300` for copyright

## Landing Page

Two sections only:
1. **Hero** — eyebrow label, oversized headline, subtitle, inline stats, single CTA, conversation demo widget
2. **Pricing** — heading, two-tier cards

No feature grids, no how-it-works, no testimonials, no waitlist, no trades list.

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Hardcoded color classes (`bg-orange-500`)
- ❌ Shadows on anything except CTA buttons
- ❌ Badges as labels — use plain `text-sm uppercase tracking-widest` text
- ❌ Icon containers with colored backgrounds (e.g. `bg-primary/10 rounded-xl` wrapping an icon)
- ❌ Multiple CTAs competing for attention in the same section
- ❌ `variant="secondary"` on any component
- ❌ Icon margins inside buttons (`mr-2`)
- ❌ `disabled` instead of `isLoading`
- ❌ Pure white (`#fff`) backgrounds — use `#fafafa`
- ❌ Small headline sizes (`text-3xl` or below for hero h1)
- ❌ Heavy font weights on body text
- ❌ Decorative elements that don't serve a function
- ❌ `CheckCircle2` or any circle-check icons — use `Check` from lucide-react instead
